name: Rename/backup a CLI binary via sudo mv in Ghostty
description: In Ghostty (terminal), execute a sudo mv command to rename/backup an installed binary by moving it from a source path to a destination path (commonly appending -old). Steps: focus terminal, paste the mv command with paths, press Enter.
